36 Ophiuchi.label: 36 Ophiuchi
36 Ophiuchi.description: 36 Ophiuchi is a triple star system 19.5 light years away from Earth. It is in the constellation Ophiuchus. Wikipedia

77 Aquarii.label: 77 Aquarii
77 Aquarii.description: 77 Aquarii is the Flamsteed designation for a star in the equatorial constellation of Aquarius. It has an apparent visual magnitude of 5.55 and is around 134 light-years from Earth. This is a giant star with a stellar classification of K1 III. Wikipedia

BZ Crucis.label: HD 110432
BZ Crucis.description: HD 110432 is a Be star in the constellation Crux, behind the southern Coalsack Nebula. It has a stellar classification of B1IVe, which means it is a subgiant star of class B that displays emission lines in its spectrum. Wikipedia

11 Aquarii.label: 11 Aquarii
11 Aquarii.description: 11 Aquarii is a sunlike star in the constellation Aquarius with an apparent magnitude is 6.22. It is approximately 86 ly from Earth and is a main-sequence star of spectral type G1 and luminosity class ... Wikipedia

Zeta Crucis.label: Zeta Crucis
Zeta Crucis.description: ζ Crucis is a binary star in the constellation Crux. It has an apparent magnitude of 4.06m. The primary star is classified as a blue-white dwarf. The secondary component is much fainter, with an apparent magnitude of 12.49. Wikipedia

OGLE2-TR-L9.label: OGLE2-TR-L9
OGLE2-TR-L9.description: OGLE2-TR-L9 is a magnitude 15 star in the constellation Carina at a distance of approximately 2,935 light years. Wikipedia

GJ 3634.label: GJ 3634
GJ 3634.description: GJ 3634 is a red dwarf star in the Hydra constellation. One planet has been discovered in its orbit, GJ 3634 b. Wikipedia

BD +20°307.label: BD +20°307
BD +20°307.description: BD +20°307 is a close binary star system approximately 300 light-years away in the constellation Aries. The system is surrounded by a dusty ring. Wikipedia

Gliese 436.label: Gliese 436
Gliese 436.description: Gliese 436 is a red dwarf approximately 33.1 light-years away in the zodiac constellation of Leo. It has an apparent visual magnitude of 10.67, which is much too faint to be seen with the naked eye. Wikipedia

R Scuti.label: R Scuti
R Scuti.description:
R Scuti is a star in the constellation of Scutum. It is a yellow supergiant and is a pulsating variable known as a RV Tauri variable.
It was discovered in 1795 by Edward Pigott at a time when only a few variable stars were known to exist. Wikipedia

V725 Sagittarii.label: V725 Sagittarii
V725 Sagittarii.description: V725 Sagittarii is a semiregular pulsating variable star in the constellation of Sagittarius. As recently as a century ago, it was a Population II Cepheid; its transformation was documented by Henrietta ... Wikipedia

GX 339-4.label: GX 339-4
GX 339-4.description: GX 339-4 is a moderately strong variable galactic low-mass X-ray binary source and black-hole candidate that flares from time to time. Wikipedia

HAT-P-5.label: HAT-P-5
HAT-P-5.description: HAT-P-5 is a 12th magnitude star in the constellation Lyra, approximately 1,100 light years away from Earth. It is a spectral type G star, about 1.16 solar masses and radii greater than our Sun, and only 200 Kelvins hotter. Wikipedia

Centaurus X-3.label: Centaurus X-3
Centaurus X-3.description: Centaurus X-3 is an X-ray pulsar with a period of 4.84 seconds. It was the first X-ray pulsar to be discovered, and the third X-ray source to be discovered in the constellation Centaurus. Wikipedia

OGLE-TR-182.label: OGLE-TR-182
OGLE-TR-182.description: OGLE-TR-182 is a dim magnitude 17 star far off in the constellation Carina at a distance of approximately 12,700 light years. Wikipedia

Theta Lyrae.label: Theta Lyrae
Theta Lyrae.description: Theta Lyrae is a star in a trinary star system, in the constellation Lyra, approximately 770 light years away from Earth. Wikipedia

OGLE-TR-56.label: OGLE-TR-56
OGLE-TR-56.description: OGLE-TR-56 is a dim, distant, magnitude 17 Sun-like star located approximately 1500 parsecs away in the constellation of Sagittarius. Wikipedia

SGR 1627-41.label: SGR 1627-41
SGR 1627-41.description: SGR 1627-41, is a soft gamma repeater, located in the constellation of Norma. It was discovered June 15, 1998 using the Burst and transient Source Experiment and was the first soft gamma repeater to be discovered since 1979. Wikipedia

RX J0822-4300.label: RX J0822-4300
RX J0822-4300.description: RX J0822-4300, often referred to as a "Cosmic Cannonball", is a radio-quiet neutron star currently moving away from the center of the Puppis A supernova remnant at over 3 million miles per hour, making it one of the fastest moving stars ever found. Wikipedia

BT Monocerotis.label: BT Monocerotis
BT Monocerotis.description: BT Monocerotis was a nova, which lit up in the constellation Monoceros in 1939. It was discovered on a spectral plate by Fred L. Whipple on December 23, 1939. BT Monocerotis reached a brightness of 4.5 mag. Wikipedia

XTE J1739-285.label: XTE J1739-285
XTE J1739-285.description: XTE J1739-285 is a neutron star, in the constellation Ophiuchus, situated approximately 39,000 light-years from Earth. It was first observed on 19 October 1999 by NASA's Rossi X-ray Timing Explorer satellite. Wikipedia

V1280 Scorpii.label: V1280 Scorpii
V1280 Scorpii.description: V1280 Scorpii is a nova observed in February 2007 in the constellation Scorpius, just south of M62. The nova was a 9th magnitude object when it was discovered independently by Yuji Nakamura and Yukio ... Wikipedia

PSR J0737-3039.label: PSR J0737-3039
PSR J0737-3039.description: PSR J0737-3039 is the only known double pulsar, it consists of two neutron stars emitting electromagnetic waves in the radio wavelength in a relativistic binary system. The two Pulsars are known as PSR J0737-3039A and PSR J0737-3039B. Wikipedia

BD +17° 3248.label: BD +17° 3248
BD +17° 3248.description: BD +17° 3248 is an old Population II star located at a distance of roughly 968 light-years in the Galactic Halo. It belongs to the class of ultra-metal-poor stars, especially the very rare subclass of neutron-capture enhanced stars. Wikipedia

Tycho G.label: Tycho G
Tycho G.description:
Tycho G is the surviving binary companion star of the SN 1572 supernova event.
The star is located about 7500 light-years away in the constellation Cassiopeia. It is a subgiant, similar to our Sun in luminosity and color but more evolved. Wikipedia

GD 66.label: GD 66
GD 66.description: GD 66 or V361 Aurigae is a 0.64 solar mass pulsating white dwarf star located 170 light years from Earth in the Auriga constellation. The estimated cooling age of the white dwarf is 500 million years. Wikipedia

R Canum Venaticorum.label: R Canum Venaticorum
R Canum Venaticorum.description: R Canum Venaticorum is a Mira variable star. Wikipedia

GK Persei.label: GK Persei
GK Persei.description: GK Persei was a bright nova occurring in 1901. It reached a maximum magnitude of 0.2, the brightest nova of modern times until Nova Aquilae 1918. Wikipedia

2MASS J04414489+2301513.label: 2MASS J04414489+2301513
2MASS J04414489+2301513.description: 2MASS J04414489+2301513 is a young brown dwarf approximately 450 light years away with an orbiting companion about 5–10 times the mass of Jupiter. Wikipedia

HAT-P-7.label: HAT-P-7
HAT-P-7.description: HAT-P-7 is a yellow white dwarf star located about 1044 light-years away in the constellation Cygnus. Wikipedia

AG Carinae.label: AG Carinae
AG Carinae.description: AG Carinae is a star in the constellation Carina. It is classified as a luminous blue variable and is one of the most luminous stars in the Milky Way. Wikipedia

GSC 03089-00929.label: GSC 03089-00929
GSC 03089-00929.description: GSC 03089-00929 is a magnitude 12 star located approximately 1300 light-years away in the constellation of Hercules. This star is a G type main sequence star that is similar to but slightly cooler than our sun. Wikipedia

BD+20°2457.label: BD+20°2457
BD+20°2457.description: BD+20°2457 is a 10th magnitude K-type bright giant star located between 320 to 980 light years away in the constellation of Leo. Wikipedia

Alpha Pictoris.label: Alpha Pictoris
Alpha Pictoris.description: Alpha Pictoris is the brightest star in the southern constellation of Pictor. It has an apparent visual magnitude of 3.27, which is bright enough to be viewed from urban areas in the southern hemisphere. Wikipedia

Kepler-8.label: Kepler-8
Kepler-8.description: Kepler-8 is a star located in the constellation Lyra in the field of view of the Kepler Mission, a NASA-led operation tasked with discovering terrestrial planets. Wikipedia

KY Cygni.label: KY Cygni
KY Cygni.description: KY Cygni is a red supergiant star located in the constellation Cygnus. It is one of the largest stars known, at about 1,420 or more times the Sun's diameter, and is also one of the most luminous, with ... Wikipedia

HL Tau 76.label: HL Tau 76
HL Tau 76.description: HL Tau 76 is a variable white dwarf star of the DAV type. It was observed by G. Haro and W. J. Luyten in 1961, and was the first variable white dwarf discovered when, in 1968, Arlo U. Landolt found that ... Wikipedia

Kepler-5.label: Kepler-5
Kepler-5.description: Kepler-5 is a star located in the constellation Cygnus in the field of view of the Kepler Mission, a NASA project aimed at detecting planets in transit of, or passing in front of, their host stars as seen from Earth. Wikipedia

OGLE-TR-122.label: OGLE-TR-122
OGLE-TR-122.description: OGLE-TR-122 is a binary stellar system containing one of the smallest main-sequence stars whose radius has been measured. Wikipedia

PG 1159-035.label: PG 1159-035
PG 1159-035.description: PG 1159-035 is the prototypical PG 1159 star after which the class of PG 1159 stars was named. It was discovered in the Palomar-Green survey of ultraviolet-excess stellar objects and, like the other PG ... Wikipedia

PSR J0537-6910.label: PSR J0537-6910
PSR J0537-6910.description: PSR J0537-6910 is a pulsar that is 4,000 years old, and about 170,000 light years away, in the southern sky. It rotates at 62 Hertz. Wikipedia

PSR B1919+21.label: PSR B1919+21
PSR B1919+21.description: PSR B1919+21 is a pulsar with a period of 1.3373 seconds, and a pulse width of 0.04 second. It was the first radio pulsar discovered. Wikipedia

R Hydrae.label: R Hydrae
R Hydrae.description:
R Hydrae, also known as R Hya, is a Mira-type variable star in the constellation Hydra.
The magnitude of R Hydrae varies over a period of 389 days, between 3.21 and 11.00. The period of R Hydrae changes slowly. Wikipedia

Ross 154.label: Ross 154
Ross 154.description: Ross 154 is a star in the southern zodiac constellation of Sagittarius. It has an apparent visual magnitude of 10.44, making it much too faint to be seen with the naked eye. Wikipedia

S2 (star).label: S2
S2 (star).description: Source 2, also known as S0—2, is a star that is located close to the radio source Sagittarius A*, orbiting it with an orbital period of 15.56 ± 0.35 years and a pericenter distance of 17 light hours — ... Wikipedia

R136b.label: R136b
R136b.description: R136b is a Wolf-Rayet star in the Large Magellanic Cloud. Wikipedia

VB 10.label: VB 10
VB 10.description: VB 10, also referred to as Van Biesbroeck's star, is a very small and very dim M-type red dwarf located in the constellation Aquila. Wikipedia

WR 104.label: WR 104
WR 104.description: WR 104 is a Wolf-Rayet star discovered in 1998, located 8,000 light years from Earth. It is a binary star with an OB companion. Wikipedia

Var 83.label: Var
Var 83.description: The Var is a department in the Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur region in Provence in southeastern France. It takes its name from the river Var, which used to flow along its eastern boundary, but the boundary was moved in 1860. Wikipedia

AM Canum Venaticorum.label: AM Canum Venaticorum
AM Canum Venaticorum.description: AM Canum Venaticorum is a cataclysmic variable binary star in the constellation of Canes Venatici. It is the type star of its class of variables, the AM CVn stars. Wikipedia

GJ 1061.label: GJ 1061
GJ 1061.description: GJ 1061 is a small red dwarf approximately 12 light-years from Earth in the southern constellation of Horologium. Wikipedia

BD+60 2522.label: BD+60 2522
BD+60 2522.description: SAO 20575 or BD+60°2522 is a bright O-class star that has produced the Bubble Nebula with its stellar wind. Wikipedia

HIP 13044.label: HIP 13044
HIP 13044.description: HIP 13044 is a red horizontal-branch star about 2,300 light years away from the Earth in the constellation Fornax. The star is part of the Helmi stream, a former dwarf galaxy that merged with the Milky Way between six and nine billion years ago. Wikipedia

PSR B1829−10.label: PSR B1829−10
PSR B1829−10.description: PSR B1829-10 is a pulsar that is approximately 30,000 light-years away in the constellation of Scutum. This pulsar has been the target of interest, because of a mistaken identification of a planet around it. Wikipedia

TZ Arietis.label: TZ Arietis
TZ Arietis.description: TZ Arietis is the variable star designation for a red dwarf star in the northern constellation of Aries. Wikipedia

T Cephei.label: T Cephei
T Cephei.description: T Cephei is a Mira variable giant star in the constellation Cepheus. With its radius of 540 solar radii, it is one of the larger known stars. Wikipedia

GD 362.label: GD 362
GD 362.description: GD 362 is a white dwarf approximately 150 light years from Earth. In 2004, spectroscopic observations showed that it had a relatively high concentration of metals in its atmosphere. Wikipedia

AR Cassiopeiae.label: AR Cassiopeiae
AR Cassiopeiae.description: AR Cassiopeiae is a multiple star system in the constellation of Cassiopeia. It is thought to be a septuple star system. Wikipedia

PSR B0950+08.label: PSR B0950+08
PSR B0950+08.description: The pulsar PSR B0950+08 seems to have come from a supernova that occurred in Leo 1.8 million years ago. The remnant of this supernova may be the nearest besides the Local Bubble, and the supernova would have been as bright as the moon. Wikipedia

G29-38.label: G 29-38
G29-38.description: Giclas 29-38 is a variable white dwarf star of the DAV, or ZZ Ceti, whose variability is due to large-amplitude, non-radial pulsations, known as gravity waves. It was first reported to be variable by Shulov and Kopatskaya in 1974. Wikipedia

108 Aquarii.label: 108 Aquarii
108 Aquarii.description: 108 Aquarii is the Flamsteed designation for a star in the equatorial constellation of Aquarius. It has an apparent visual magnitude of 5.194 and can be seen with the naked eye under suitably dark skies. Wikipedia

Eta1 Doradus.label: Eta1 Doradus
Eta1 Doradus.description: Eta¹ Doradus is the Bayer designation for an A-type main sequence star in the constellation of Dorado, around 330 light-years from the Earth. It has an apparent visual magnitude of approximately 5.697. Wikipedia

Gamma Ophiuchi.label: Gamma Ophiuchi
Gamma Ophiuchi.description:
Gamma Ophiuchi is a fourth-magnitude star in the constellation Ophiuchus. It is located about 95 light-years from Earth. The system has an age of roughly 184 million years.
This is an A-type main sequence star with a stellar classification of A0 V. Wikipedia

9 Sagittarii.label: 9 Sagittarii
9 Sagittarii.description: 9 Sagittarii is an emission-line star in Sagittarius. It has a spectral type of O4V. Wikipedia
